Viridian Genesis NFT
 This contract is designed to be used on our genesis Ethereum mint and future drops on the same contract, it is extremely gas efficient for minting multiple packs.
 If this contract can be upgradable and/or be upgradable it could be converted to our main infrastructure contract.

Viridian Genesis NFT
 This contract is designed to be used on our genesis Ethereum mint and future drops on the same contract, it is extremely gas efficient for minting multiple packs.
 If this contract can be upgradable and/or be upgradable it could be converted to our main infrastructure contract.

addAdmin(address).details: Owner can add new admins addresses if exchange is upgraded.

adminMint(uint256[],address,bool).details: Admin addresses can manually mint NFTs either unrevealed or revealed. This will primarily be used for getting submissions onto the exchange.

allowOpening().details: Enables users to be able to open their NFTs.

crossmintMint(uint8,address).details: Users can mint with USD on crossmint during the drop for a convenience fee (ex: Ether on Ethereum).

freezeOpening().details: Disables the ability to open NFTs.

initialize(address,address,string,string.details: Set the original default opened and unopenend base URI. Also set the forwarder for gaseless and the treasury address.

isAddressWhitelisted(address).details: Returns whether the address is on the whitelist.

isApprovedForAll(address,address).details: Overridden version of isApprovedForAll where the admins (exchange addresses) are always approved

isOpeningUnlocked().details: Returns whether users are able to open their NFTs.

isPublicMintingEnabled().details: Returns whether the public minting period has started.

isTokenOpeningUnlocked(uint256).details: Returns whether users are able to open their NFTs.

isWhitelistMintingEnabled().details: Returns whether the whitelist minting period has started.

mint(uint8,address).details: Users can mint during the drop using the blockchains native currency (ex: Ether on Ethereum).

newDrop(uint16,uint256,string,string).details: Start a new drop while leaving the previous drops alone.

open(uint256).details: Allows user to open an NFT and reveal the contents.

openTo(uint256,address).details: Allows user to open an NFT and reveal the contents, then have it transferred to a different address. This will be primarily used by streamers to open up packs their audience has purcahsed.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

removeAdmin(address).details: Owner can remove permissions from depreciated admin addresses.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setBaseURI(string).details: Admin can change base URI for unopened NFTs.

setBaseURIOpened(string).details: Admin can change base URI for openend NFTs.

setHashedTokenIds(uint256[],uint256,uint.details: Owner can set the hashed tokenIds.

setMintPrice(uint256).details: Owner can change the mint price for one NFT.

setPublicMinting(bool).details: Enables the ability for any addresses to begin minting.

setTreasury(address).details: Owner can change the treasury address.

setTrustedForwarder(address).details: Owner can change the trusted forwarder used for gasless.

setWhitelist(address[],uint8).details: Owner can set the whitelist addresses and how many NFTs each whitelist member can mint.

setWhitelistMinting(bool).details: Enables the ability for addresses on the whitelist to begin minting.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

burn(uint256).notice: Destroy the NFT with the given token Id.

isTrustedForwarder(address).notice: return if the forwarder is trusted to forward relayed transactions to us. the forwarder is required to verify the sender's signature, and verify the call is not a replay.

tokenURI(uint256).notice: Returns the token URI which will be different dependent on whether the NFT has been opened.

If this contract can be upgradable and/or be upgradable it could be converted to our main infrastructure contract.
